To fix this code quality issue, we should remove or comment out the console.log statement from the production code. 

Here's an example of how you can do this:

```typescript
// console.log('Some debugging information...');

// Or remove the console.log statement completely
// This line should be removed before deploying to production
// console.log('Some debugging information...');
```

By removing or commenting out the console.log statement, we ensure that no debugging information is printed to the console in the production environment.